Author: cipi#4502
Content: it says `virtual memory exhausted` ... -j8 is too much, since every compile thread will use 1GB RAM and more, so if you don't have a lot of RAM, you should lower the value... try with -j4 or less

Author: SlhCn#0104
Content: i have 4gb ram only..

Author: cipi#4502
Content: i suppose there are also some things running on this computer, that also uses some of the 4GB... i would remove the `-j` option completely, so just do `./zcutil/build.sh`, just to be sure you are not running out of RAM during compile

Author: cipi#4502
Content: ooops... weird error... `undefined reference` to whatever... could be that the last compile produced some corrupted files... you could try to either `git clone` from scratch and thus also compile from scratch... or maybe `make clean` and then `./zcutil/build.sh` again

Author: cipi#4502
Content: with `last compile`i mean the one that crashed with `out of memory` ... when RAM gets full, weird things can happen
